   <refnamediv>
       <refname>hypg_rnd  </refname>
               <refpurpose>hypergeometric random draws </refpurpose>
   </refnamediv>
 
        <refsynopsisdiv>
               <title>CALLING SEQUENCE</title>
               <synopsis>[x]=hypg_rnd(nobs,n,K,N)</synopsis>
        </refsynopsisdiv>
 
        <refsection>
           <title>PARAMETERS</title>
           <variablelist>
           <varlistentry>
 
           <term>Input</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> nobs </term> =    number of draws</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>*  <term> n,K,N </term> =    parameters of the distribution</para></listitem>
 
 
 
<listitem><para>&#160;</para></listitem>
 
           </varlistentry>
 
          <varlistentry>
 
          <term>Output</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> x </term> =    a vector of random draws from the distribution</para></listitem>
 
 
          </varlistentry>
          </variablelist>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
Returns hypergeometric random draws
prob(X=x) =  (N)^-1  (K) (N-K)
                     (n)         (x)  (n-x)
<para>NOTE: mean = (n/N)*k ; variance = [(n*K)/(N*N)*(N-1)]*(N-K)*(N-n) </para>
<para> </para>
 
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>EXAMPLE</title>
              <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
p=hypg_pdf(100,15,20,30)
 
               ]]></programlisting>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>AUTHOR</title>
Eric Dubois 2002
        </refsection>
</refentry>
